<br>
(this isnt directed at you Arcus, its just you talking about tailoring reminded me of it)<br>
<br>
I don't mind making people in the guild armor. However, its not the primary reason I became a tailor, and stopping to make people armor is time away from what I am trying to do (make money to buy an emblem).<br>
<br>
I would really appreciate therefore, if people want armor from me, if they would do a little research beforehand.<br>
<br>
I dont know what armor cons what color to what level. So asking me for a &quot;set of yellow armor&quot; is no good.<br>
<br>
An example of what I need is:<br>
<br>
&quot;Hi Zad, are you free to make me some armor? I need cured siluric. Arms, Gloves, Helm and Leggings (no jerkin or boots). How much would that cost?&quot;<br>
<br>
That kind of question I can answer pretty quick, only takes me a minute to look at the recipes for the peices and work out the component cost.<br>
<br>
Secondly, be prepared to put in a little work yourself to get the armor made. Don't expect me to travel to you to deliver it, or expect me to drop everything while out hunting to go to camelot to buy components to make it for you.<br>
<br>
If I am in Camelot, then come to me to get it made, and that means come to the location in Camelot where I am, not expect me to come and find you. If I am out hunting, then I will happily still make you some armor.. IF you ask me what the material requirements are, and then YOU buy them from the vendor and travel to me, I will make what you need 'in the field' for you.<br>
<br>
Anyway, rant over....<br>
<br>
