<br>
What I can help with is what type of armour people need to try and buy.<br>
<br>
First, as the tailors already know, there are 3 different types of armour we can make (roman, cyrmic and siluric) and we can make each of those out of 7-8 different materials. The materials are rawhide, tanned, cured, hard, rigid, embossed, imbued.<br>
<br>
Each specific piece of armour has a skill requirement to make it. This skill requirement can basically be translated into what it will con to you. After talking to several people and making armour for others I have found that armour that takes a skill level of around 25-30 times your charachter level will give you nice yellow armour. If you buy all one kind of armour (cured siluric for example) then it will all be yellow at the same time but the gloves will blue out first, followed by the helm, boots, leggs sleves and finally the vest.<br>
<br>
So, like Zad said, if you want armour to be made for you then take your level times 30 and go to <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.daoctradeskills.com">www.daoctradeskills.com</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->, go to the tailoring section and start comparing AF and skill levels. I'd choose the armour group that had the jerkin close to 30 times your levels. That would put the gloves around the 25 times your level.<br>
<br>
This 30 times your level thing might put you in an orange piece or two but it's the best round number I have found. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm14.showPrevMessage?topicID=102.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm14.showNextMessage?topicID=102.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=102.topic&index=3><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm14.emailToFriend?topicID=102.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm14.threadControl?topicID=102.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm14.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=102.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm14.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=102.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub35.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="monklybusiness43508frm13">Board Rules<option value="monklybusiness43508frm17">Monk Change<option value="monklybusiness43508frm1">General<option v